How to install Python Multi Version on MAC OS
≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠≠


1. Install Brew 
    Open Terminal paste this code:  /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

2. Install Pyenv
    brew install pyenv

3. Install Python (with your version)
    pyenv install (Python Version)
    Example : pyenv install 3.8.19

4. Make your shell "Terminal" run pyenv
    Open Terminal "Make sure you're in home location directory"
    paste this code :  vi .bash_profile  or  vi .zshrc
    press "enter" to write
    
    Paste this code : if command -v pyenv 1>/dev/null 2>&1; then
                        eval "$(pyenv init -)"
                      fi
    
    press "esc" after write
    press and hold " Shift + Z " for save [ Press double " Z " for save & quit ]

5. Terminate your terminal
    Check with command : python -V


Thank You,
Hopefully will help you,
